into the brachiocephalic vein

527
00:26:38,852 --> 00:26:40,552
and on to the superior vena cava.

528
00:26:40,554 --> 00:26:43,220
If it punctured the SVC,
blood could be leaking

529
00:26:43,222 --> 00:26:45,148
behind the heart,
restricting the heart's ability

530
00:26:45,179 --> 00:26:47,091
to expand and fill during diastole,

531
00:26:47,093 --> 00:26:48,559
reducing the heart's efficiency.

532
00:26:48,682 --> 00:26:51,015
[Smacks lips] Lot of ifs there.

533
00:26:51,730 --> 00:26:56,132
♪♪

534
00:26:56,134 --> 00:27:00,407
Dr. Chen, pair of 14-gauge on a syringe.

535
00:27:00,505 --> 00:27:04,507
♪♪

536
00:27:04,626 --> 00:27:07,710
All in favor of ratifying
Dr. Glassman's decision

537
00:27:07,805 --> 00:27:09,881
in hiring Dr. Shaun Murphy?

538
00:27:14,218 --> 00:27:15,218
All against.

539
00:27:19,535 --> 00:27:20,737
[Knocks] Excuse me.

540
00:27:20,762 --> 00:27:22,094
Is this a medical emergency?

541
00:27:22,119 --> 00:27:23,228
No. No medical emergency...

542
00:27:23,253 --> 00:27:24,756
Then you weren't
supposed to interrupt...

543
00:27:24,782 --> 00:27:26,536
Yes, I know, but you need to go online.

544
00:27:26,562 --> 00:27:28,574
- What? What site?
- Pretty much any of them...

545
00:27:28,707 --> 00:27:31,477
Twitter, YouTube, any local news site.

546
00:27:31,613 --> 00:27:36,649
♪♪

547
00:27:36,651 --> 00:27:38,418
<i>He saved his life!</i>

548
00:27:38,420 --> 00:27:39,420
[<i> Applause</i>]

549
00:27:42,389 --> 00:27:45,262
The YouTube clip already has
over 200,000 views.

550
00:27:45,340 --> 00:27:47,150
Apparently, he's one of our doctors.

551
00:27:48,574 --> 00:27:51,417
Dr. Shaun Murphy saved this boy?

552
00:27:52,328 --> 00:27:54,464
The boy is in O.R. 2.

553
00:27:54,807 --> 00:27:57,243
Dr. Melendez isn't sure
if he's going to make it.

554
00:27:58,504 --> 00:28:06,504
♪♪

555
00:28:07,714 --> 00:28:10,168
Your fiancé sure can handle a knife.

556
00:28:12,362 --> 00:28:14,733
Why did you warn me about
respecting Dr. Andrews?

557
00:28:14,969 --> 00:28:15,969
[Smacks lips]

558
00:28:19,055 --> 00:28:20,354
What's going on?

559
00:28:20,449 --> 00:28:22,494
I'm not gonna always
be here to protect you.

560
00:28:23,142 --> 00:28:24,748
You think you're gonna lose?

561
00:28:26,392 --> 00:28:28,257
Everybody loses...

562
00:28:28,810 --> 00:28:30,064
eventually.

563
00:28:33,170 --> 00:28:34,627
Is that your guy?

564
00:28:35,740 --> 00:28:43,679
♪♪

565
00:28:43,681 --> 00:28:51,396
♪♪

566
00:28:51,527 --> 00:28:53,527
Can we get a TV?

567
00:28:53,736 --> 00:28:54,736
No.

568
00:28:55,223 --> 00:28:56,385
Why not?

569
00:28:57,327 --> 00:28:59,327
Because we're poor, dude.

570
00:28:59,399 --> 00:29:01,269
We live in a bus.

571
00:29:02,761 --> 00:29:05,214
Do you think Mom is looking for us?

572
00:29:05,441 --> 00:29:06,441
Nope.

573
00:29:10,773 --> 00:29:14,887
She loves us, but she knows
it's better this way.

574
00:29:16,745 --> 00:29:24,745
♪♪

575
00:29:26,280 --> 00:29:27,927
I got you a present.

576
00:29:28,302 --> 00:29:29,705
It's not my birthday.

577
00:29:29,995 --> 00:29:31,332
I got you a present anyway.

578
00:29:33,695 --> 00:29:41,666
♪♪

579
00:29:41,668 --> 00:29:49,553
♪♪

580
00:29:49,578 --> 00:29:50,578
Here.

581
00:29:51,645 --> 00:29:55,146
♪♪

582
00:29:55,148 --> 00:29:56,148
[Clattering]

583
00:29:57,951 --> 00:30:05,951
♪♪

584
00:30:07,026 --> 00:30:15,026
♪♪

585
00:30:16,034 --> 00:30:24,034
♪♪

586
00:30:25,010 --> 00:30:33,010
♪♪

587
00:30:33,937 --> 00:30:34,937
Kelly.

588
00:30:36,453 --> 00:30:44,453
♪♪

589
00:30:46,462 --> 00:30:50,662
♪♪

590
00:30:51,815 --> 00:30:53,275
Dr. Browne...

591
00:30:57,540 --> 00:30:58,840
You were right.

592
00:31:01,109 --> 00:31:02,109
[Chuckles softly]

593
00:31:03,112 --> 00:31:08,481
♪♪

594
00:31:08,483 --> 00:31:13,887
♪♪

595
00:31:17,992 --> 00:31:19,958
- I don't like pickles.
- I know.

596
00:31:19,984 --> 00:31:22,431
- I don't want pickles.
- And I checked.

597
00:31:24,891 --> 00:31:27,501
You saved that boy's life.

598
00:31:27,946 --> 00:31:29,279
Oh, good.

599
00:31:29,646 --> 00:31:31,017
His name is Adam.

600
00:31:31,164 --> 00:31:32,955
Traumatic pneumothorax.

601
00:31:33,833 --> 00:31:35,542
I'm hungry.

602
00:31:39,172 --> 00:31:41,405
Board reconvenes in 45 minutes.

603
00:31:45,844 --> 00:31:47,964
Can you stay here until I get back?

604
00:31:49,752 --> 00:31:50,752
Okay.

605
00:31:53,519 --> 00:31:54,519
Okay.

606
00:31:54,599 --> 00:31:55,599
[Clears throat]

607
00:32:02,571 --> 00:32:04,111
He's got a serious deficit.

608
00:32:04,137 --> 00:32:06,354
A child is alive today
because of that deficit.

609
00:32:06,550 --> 00:32:08,385
And tomorrow, one may
be dead because of it.

610
00:32:08,499 --> 00:32:10,566
I seem to remember that
when I hired you,

611
00:32:10,568 --> 00:32:14,407
you weren't exactly making
the most adult decisions.

612
00:32:14,510 --> 00:32:16,769
You haven't killed anyone yet. Have you?

613
00:32:17,237 --> 00:32:19,441
Well, thankfully,
there's a cure for youth

614
00:32:19,443 --> 00:32:21,743
and stupidity... time and experience.

615
00:32:21,745 --> 00:32:24,558
[Laughs] There's a cure
for stupidity? Okay.

616
00:32:24,980 --> 00:32:26,849
That would be a windfall.

617
00:32:27,217 --> 00:32:29,436
All Shaun has is a diagnosis.

618
00:32:31,645 --> 00:32:33,070
I'd like your help.

619
00:32:33,543 --> 00:32:35,394
I take it I'm not gonna get it.

620
00:32:36,993 --> 00:32:37,993
Okay.

621
00:32:38,938 --> 00:32:39,938
[Door opens]

622
00:32:39,984 --> 00:32:40,984
Wait.

623
00:32:41,841 --> 00:32:43,607
What's the story with this kid?

624
00:32:43,672 --> 00:32:45,646
Why is it so important to you?

625
00:32:46,002 --> 00:32:47,002
[Sighs]

626
00:32:47,703 --> 00:32:48,703
Why not?

627
00:32:49,364 --> 00:32:52,138
Because letting things
get personal is a sure formula

628
00:32:52,140 --> 00:32:53,842
for screwing things up.

629
00:32:55,210 --> 00:32:56,443
I don't know.

630
00:32:56,567 --> 00:32:59,341
Letting things get personal is how we...

631
00:32:59,681 --> 00:33:02,359
[sighs]...how we make it matter.

632
00:33:05,519 --> 00:33:06,519
[Sighs]

633
00:33:10,891 --> 00:33:13,710
So, are you proud or disappointed?

634
00:33:14,590 --> 00:33:16,550
Do I have to pick just one?

635
00:33:17,131 --> 00:33:22,914
♪♪

636
00:33:23,936 --> 00:33:24,936
Hey.

637
00:33:27,987 --> 00:33:29,740
You're new to town, right?

638
00:33:30,256 --> 00:33:31,256
Yes.

639
00:33:31,478 --> 00:33:33,511
Well, I'm sure you have
a lot of questions.

640
00:33:33,739 --> 00:33:34,739
No.

641
00:33:36,221 --> 00:33:37,221
Uh...

642
00:33:38,215 --> 00:33:41,302
You got to be curious about
the place, about the people.

643
00:33:41,328 --> 00:33:43,895
Dr. Glassman gave me
a map of the hospital,

644
00:33:43,921 --> 00:33:46,382
and I got a map of San Jose online.

645
00:33:49,294 --> 00:33:50,494
[Chuckles] Okay.

646
00:33:51,694 --> 00:33:52,694
Great.

647
00:33:58,045 --> 00:33:59,911
I do have one question.

648
00:33:59,937 --> 00:34:00,937
Yeah?

649
00:34:03,241 --> 00:34:05,681
Why were you rude to me
when we first met,

650
00:34:05,728 --> 00:34:07,643
then nicer to me the second time we met,

651
00:34:07,645 --> 00:34:09,278
and now you want to be my friend?

652
00:34:10,281 --> 00:34:13,119
Which time was it
that you were pretending?

653
00:34:16,551 --> 00:34:18,891
Shaun. We're ready.

654
00:34:20,223 --> 00:34:26,297
♪♪

655
00:34:26,729 --> 00:34:29,581
The vote was clear.
Why are we reopening this?

656
00:34:29,607 --> 00:34:31,598
Is it really because
of a piece of publicity?

657
00:34:31,600 --> 00:34:33,767
It's because the man just
saved somebody's life.

658
00:34:33,769 --> 00:34:35,069
And thank God for that,

659
00:34:35,071 --> 00:34:36,851
but it doesn't change
a single thing we discussed.

660
00:34:36,877 --> 00:34:38,400
Glassman: Give him six months.

661
00:34:38,473 --> 00:34:41,475
If he proves anything
less than excellent...

662
00:34:41,477 --> 00:34:44,053
Someone "less than excellent"
means someone else dies.

663
00:34:44,131 --> 00:34:46,807
Well, I-I would love
to make you happy, Doctor.

664
00:34:46,832 --> 00:34:49,983
I would love to hire someone
who never, ever makes a mistake.

665
00:34:49,985 --> 00:34:52,885
Unfortunately, God already has a job.

666
00:34:53,171 --> 00:34:55,254
I can accept that he will have insights

667
00:34:55,256 --> 00:34:57,224
that none of the rest of us will have.

668
00:34:57,405 --> 00:34:59,092
Can you accept that
he will make mistakes

669
00:34:59,094 --> 00:35:00,414
none of the rest of us will make?

670
00:35:00,439 --> 00:35:02,042
You won't be the one who pays the price.

671
00:35:07,934 --> 00:35:12,074
If Shaun doesn't live up to
everything I know he can do,

672
00:35:12,406 --> 00:35:14,628
he will be immediately released.

673
00:35:15,160 --> 00:35:19,344
And I will resign my position
as President of this hospital.

674
00:35:21,980 --> 00:35:24,615
We haven't heard from Dr. Murphy yet.

675
00:35:25,005 --> 00:35:28,769
Perhaps we should hear from him
before we decide his fate.

676
00:35:30,055 --> 00:35:31,055
Shaun...

677
00:35:47,706 --> 00:35:49,024
Dr. Murphy...

678
00:35:50,381 --> 00:35:54,283
I'd like you to tell us why
you want to become a surgeon.

679
00:36:09,793 --> 00:36:12,627
♪♪

680
00:36:12,629 --> 00:36:14,704
Why do I want them to be my friends?

681
00:36:14,797 --> 00:36:16,720
Everybody needs friends, Shaun.

682
00:36:16,766 --> 00:36:20,268
It's gonna be cool, okay?
Play hide and seek maybe?

683
00:36:20,270 --> 00:36:22,670
- Okay.
- Tag in the warehouse?

684
00:36:22,672 --> 00:36:28,175
♪♪

685
00:36:28,177 --> 00:36:30,644
Hey, stop following me.

686
00:36:30,646 --> 00:36:38,646
♪♪

687
00:36:40,622 --> 00:36:48,622
♪♪

688
00:36:50,631 --> 00:36:58,631
♪♪

689
00:37:00,708 --> 00:37:02,842
♪♪

690
00:37:02,949 --> 00:37:05,656
- Told ya it was fun, right?
- Shh!

691
00:37:06,112 --> 00:37:12,049
♪♪

692
00:37:12,051 --> 00:37:13,818
Hey, you know what?

693
00:37:13,820 --> 00:37:15,320
[Gasps, screams]

694
00:37:18,104 --> 00:37:19,104
[Thud]

695
00:37:20,959 --> 00:37:28,959
♪♪

696
00:37:30,969 --> 00:37:38,969
♪♪

697
00:37:50,921 --> 00:37:53,904
The day that the rain
smelled like ice cream,

698
00:37:55,497 --> 00:37:59,919
my bunny went to heaven
in front of my eyes.

699
00:38:03,933 --> 00:38:06,673
The day that the copper pipes
in the old building

700
00:38:06,743 --> 00:38:08,845
smelled like burnt food,

701
00:38:10,731 --> 00:38:12,111
my brother...

702
00:38:14,553 --> 00:38:17,386
went to heaven in front of my eyes.

703
00:38:21,160 --> 00:38:22,889
I couldn't save them.

704
00:38:24,073 --> 00:38:25,499
It's sad.

705
00:38:28,220 --> 00:38:31,013
Neither one had the chance
to become an adult.

706
00:38:33,166 --> 00:38:36,346
They should have become adults.

707
00:38:39,120 --> 00:38:42,134
They should have had
children of their own

708
00:38:42,478 --> 00:38:45,827
and loved those children.

709
00:38:50,310 --> 00:38:52,841
And I want to make that possible

710
00:38:53,044 --> 00:38:54,521
for other people.

711
00:38:56,216 --> 00:39:04,216
♪♪

712
00:39:05,591 --> 00:39:07,591
And I want to make a lot of money

713
00:39:07,593 --> 00:39:09,161
so that I can have a television.

714
00:39:12,031 --> 00:39:20,031
♪♪

715
00:39:20,845 --> 00:39:22,071
Dr. Murphy...

716
00:39:26,177 --> 00:39:29,378
I want to be the first to welcome you

717
00:39:29,380 --> 00:39:32,082
to San Jose St. Bonaventure Hospital.

718
00:39:32,617 --> 00:39:35,452
♪♪

719
00:39:35,454 --> 00:39:37,402
We're very proud to have you.

720
00:39:37,589 --> 00:39:39,846
[Applause]

721
00:39:41,559 --> 00:39:47,180
♪♪

722
00:39:47,484 --> 00:39:51,988
Shaun, Dr. Melendez's
team is going into surgery.

723
00:39:52,954 --> 00:39:55,721
I mean, if you're interested.

724
00:40:00,743 --> 00:40:08,743
♪♪

725
00:40:10,219 --> 00:40:18,219
♪♪

726
00:40:19,661 --> 00:40:27,661
♪♪

727
00:40:29,103 --> 00:40:37,103
♪♪

728
00:40:38,546 --> 00:40:46,546
♪♪

729
00:40:48,021 --> 00:40:56,021
♪♪

730
00:40:57,423 --> 00:40:59,285
Got a messy field here.

731
00:41:00,419 --> 00:41:01,419
Murphy.

732
00:41:02,868 --> 00:41:09,897
♪♪

733
00:41:10,079 --> 00:41:11,666
Shaun: Suction.

734
00:41:12,978 --> 00:41:18,009
♪♪

735
00:41:18,362 --> 00:41:20,926
Never forget, you're the smart one.

736
00:41:21,272 --> 00:41:22,671
You can do anything.

737
00:41:23,655 --> 00:41:25,306
And I'm proud of you, Shaun.

738
00:41:27,320 --> 00:41:32,762
♪♪

739
00:41:32,764 --> 00:41:34,797
Bet you've seen many of these.

740
00:41:37,286 --> 00:41:39,185
I remember my first.

741
00:41:40,003 --> 00:41:42,218
Kept thinking, "It doesn't get
any better than this."

742
00:41:44,340 --> 00:41:47,118
And for you, I'm afraid,
that's literally true.

743
00:41:50,113 --> 00:41:53,014
You're a nice kid,
and you're obviously very smart,

744
00:41:53,775 --> 00:41:55,307
but you don't belong here.

745
00:41:57,019 --> 00:41:58,803
So, as long as you're part of my team,

746
00:41:58,828 --> 00:42:01,880
this is all you're ever
going to be doing... suction.

747
00:42:06,996 --> 00:42:09,431
I saw a lot of surgeons
in medical school.

748
00:42:11,420 --> 00:42:13,321
You're much better than them.

749
00:42:13,347 --> 00:42:15,195
I have a lot to learn from you.

750
00:42:16,104 --> 00:42:21,897
♪♪

751
00:42:22,328 --> 00:42:24,488
You're very arrogant.

752
00:42:25,588 --> 00:42:28,165
Do you think that helps you
be a good surgeon?

753
00:42:29,450 --> 00:42:31,669
Does it hurt you as a person?

754
00:42:33,530 --> 00:42:34,837
Is it worth it?

755
00:42:36,289 --> 00:42:42,527
♪♪


